Use Emotion for stylizing components through a CSS class.

- https://emotion.sh/docs/introduction

Basic components

- [x] HGroup
- [x] VGroup
- [x] Label
- [x] Button
- [x] Arrow button
- [x] Container
- [x] ContextMenu
  - [x] Handle escape keys
    - [ ] for submenus, focus back to the submenu representing item
  - [x] Handle navigation keys
    - [x] horizontal keys open/close submenu (LTR or RTL based)
      - [ ] close for submenu
        - [ ] focus back the submenu representing item
    - [x] vertical keys navigates focus between menu items
- [ ] OptionList
  - [ ] `big?: boolean`: If `true`, displays a big elegant option list.
- [ ] TextInput
  - [ ] Bordered when the provided theme's `colors.background` is a near or equal color to `color.inputBackground`
    - https://stackoverflow.com/a/29247003/26380963
    - https://www.npmjs.com/package/color-convert
  - [ ] `icon?: "search"` (search icon is displayed at the right with a background equals `providedTheme.colors.primaryBackground`)
  - [ ] `disabled?: boolean`
- [ ] CheckBox
  - black&white
- [ ] LoadingBar (consists of horizontally moving dots)

Shortcuts

- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts

Icons

- [x] Checked icon
- [x] Bullet icon
- [ ] Search icon
- [ ] Loading icon
  - See https://stackoverflow.com/a/20371835/26380963